<ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">Democrats</ENAMEX> pounced on the ads, calling them a clumsy rehash of old charges and
predicting that they would backfire by antagonizing <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">voters</ENAMEX> who are sick of the
scandal. This is a classic case of self-fulfilling characterization. The ads
are actually far more sophisticated than the <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">Democrats</ENAMEX> admit. But if the press
buys the <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">Democrats</ENAMEX>' simplistic representation of the ads, they will indeed
